# Frontend Design — UI/UX Pro Max (Mandatory)

All frontend UI/UX work for this ERP **must** use the **ui-ux-pro-max** skill. Do not invent ad-hoc visual systems.

## Before Any UI Change

1. **Read the skill:** `.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md`
2. **Read the design system:**
   - `design-system/enterprise-erp-platform/MASTER.md`
   - If building a named page, also check `design-system/enterprise-erp-platform/pages/[page].md` (overrides MASTER)
3. **Run design searches when needed** (Windows: use `python`, not `python3`):

```bash
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<query>" --design-system -p "Enterprise ERP Platform"
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<query>" --stack nextjs
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<query>" --domain ux
```

## Locked Product Direction

- **Product:** Enterprise ERP / B2B SaaS admin
- **Style:** Data-Dense Dashboard + Swiss Minimalism
- **Stack:** Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind + ShadCN UI
- **Density:** High (dashboard). **Motion:** Subtle. **Variance:** Low/centered
- **Icons:** Lucide / Heroicons SVG only — never emoji icons

## Persist New Page Systems

When introducing a major new page pattern, persist an override:

```bash
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<query>" --design-system --persist -p "Enterprise ERP Platform" --page "<page-name>"
```

## Pre-Delivery (Required)

- [ ] Follows MASTER / page override tokens (colors, type, spacing)
- [ ] `cursor-pointer` on clickable elements; 150–300ms hover transitions
- [ ] Focus states visible; contrast ≥ 4.5:1; `prefers-reduced-motion` respected
- [ ] No AI purple/pink gradients; no dark-mode-by-default
- [ ] Responsive checks: 375 / 768 / 1024 / 1440
